node.accessibility_caption: Photo by fuck the bourgeoisie☭ in Casa Del Carajo with @the_southern_leftist. May be an illustration of 2 people and text that says 'Dictatorship Dictatorship Red'.

node.text:
i used to say “socialist” —with quotes— when referring to lefties who support dictatorships (and only decry human rights abuses by the US military but no one else) because I thought authoritarian dictatorships were antithetical to socialist values. I still think (read: know) that im right, but I stopped putting it in quotes because honesty I felt like I was in the minority and now no longer take anti-authoritarianism to be an intrinsic value of socialism. kinda sad, but at the end of the day, one does not stand in solidarity with the international working class by supporting their oppressors— left or right🤷🏼‍♀️
.
I’m guessing this will be my monthly “promote anti-authoritarianism and lose followers” rant, but here we go :)
.
#seized from @the_southern_leftist
